  "finger_focus": "Right pinky reaches up to [ ] (above ; ') and { } (Shift + [ ])",
  "tips": [
    {
      "type": "lead",
      "text": "Two pairs of brackets today, both worked by the right pinky. The square brackets pick out an item; the curly braces gather a group. They look alike at a glance, so the eye must learn which is which - and your fingers will get there first."
    },
    {
      "type": "drop",
      "text": "The square brackets sit just right of the P key, above the semicolon and apostrophe; strike [ and ] with the right pinky, no Shift. The braces share those keys: { is Shift+[, } is Shift+]. Same reach, Shift added."
    },
    {
      "type": "callout",
      "icon": "keyboard",
      "title": "Open it, close it",
      "text": "Every bracket you open, you close. Leave one hanging and the whole line breaks - in code it simply will not run. Make the pair a single habit, open and close together."
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "kind": "drill",
      "target": "[ ] [ ] [0] [1] [a] [ ] [ ]",
      "finger": "pink",
      "title": "Square brackets",
      "hint": "Right pinky, no Shift. Open then close, every time."
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "kind": "drill",
      "target": "{ } { } {1} {a} {1, 2} { } { }",
      "finger": "orange",
      "title": "Curly braces",
      "hint": "{ is Shift+[, } is Shift+]. The same reach, with Shift held."
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "kind": "drill",
      "target": "list[0] = 'first'. obj = {key: 1, val: 2}.",
      "finger": "green",
      "title": "Lists and groups",
      "hint": "Square brackets pick an item, curly braces hold the group."
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "text": "In code these do honest, daily work: square brackets index a list, curly braces wrap an object. Keep each pair matched and closed, and the structure stays clear to the next reader."
    }
  ],
  "character_tips": {
